body:
@zodiac 
`--tmpdir` is needed to create temp file at system temporary directory.
`-q` is needed to capture pure `mktemp` output.

@bolkedebruin Try to apply [this PR patch](https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/pull/1790.patch) onto master. Basically, you'll do that via `git am` and your headline will looks like: `Fix connection leak with PostgreSQL backend` - issue information will be missed. Ok, you'll read the man and found key `-k` - then you'll get `[PATCH] [AIRFLOW-191] Fix connection leak with PostgreSQL backend` as headline. Not what you really want to.

If you dump patches locally via `format-patch` you need to not forget to add `-k` option to not include `[PATCH]` thing into subject and use `-k` for `am` to not strip `[things]`. 

After few hours of pain, you'll end with regular expression and sed which, as you know, means that you have two problems now (:

@dmikov Well it depends on what you consider API. Fully moving everything over in one commit is not what I am aiming at. I would like to lay down the fundaments and then hopefully others will move things over that they require. 

We probably won't accept new functionality in new PRs that do not use the API framework.

I could definitely use some help. The swagger interface seems smart to integrate. So if you can take that on that would be nice. Also documentation on how to do the API properly needs some love (and thinking) - https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/AIRFLOW/API+Conventions .
